The '''Camarina Connection''' was a [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] faction that had its origins in the [[Eyttyrmin Batiiv]] group. After the destruction of their parent organization, these pirates found backing from former [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] dignitaries and unscrupulous [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] racketeers, and from their factory ship ''[[Black Lotus]]'', they became the center of a [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]-wide plan to produce and distribute the combat drug [[pentabenzedralyne]]. The gang's members were scattered across the galaxy, and operated on all levels of society, from [[Senator/Legends|Senators]] to street kids. As well as the drug project, they were involved in a range of criminal activities, including sabotage, kidnapping, industrial espionage and extortion.

==Behind the scenes==
The Camarina Connection appears only in an issue of the French roleplaying-game magazine [[Casus Belli (magazine)|''Casus Belli'']], and although material from this issue&mdash;including the design of the ''Black Lotus''&mdash;is closely associated with the French-illustrated [[Star Wars: Heir to the Empire (comic series)|comic adaption]] of ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'', the canonical status of the other content is unclear.

